Citation.sAbstract: In this work, we report the experimental values of densities, viscosities, and refractive indices at 298.15 K  and atmospheric pressure for the ternary and associated binary mixtures of tris(2-hydroxyethyl) methylammonium  methylsulfate + water + ethanol. Excess molar volumes and viscosity logarithm variations have  been calculated from the density and viscosity of these mixtures. The excess properties have been fitted  with two polynomial models that produced acceptable correlations.
Citation.sTitle: Viscosities and Volumetric Properties of Binary and Ternary Mixtures of Tris(2-hydroxyethyl) Methylammonium Methylsulfate + Water + Ethanol at 298.15 K
